annotations.description:
dict containing key as annotation name,
                    value being timestamp in seconds(float).

binary_annotations.description:
dict with key, value being the name and value
                           of the binary annotation being logged.

timestamp.description: timestamp of when the annotation occured in microseconds

value.description: name of the annotation, such as 'sr'

key.description: name of the annotation, such as 'http.uri'

value.description: value of the annotation, such as a URI

annotation_type.description: type of annotation, such as AnnotationType.I32

port.description: int value of the port. Defaults to 0

service_name.description: service name as a str. Defaults to 'unknown'

binary_thrift_obj_list.description: list of TBinaryProtocol objects to encode.

hex_string.description: the string representation of a zipkin ID

max_payload_bytes.description: max payload size in bytes. You often don't

sample_rate.description: Float between 0.0 and 100.0 to determine sampling rate
